
/*
 * The code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to a specified location. It retrieves nodes from the [.arguments] node, specifically [order] and [direction], using the [get-nodes] slot and appends them to the [data.read] node. This is useful for dynamically constructing or modifying a node structure based on input arguments. 
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Appends nodes to the specified location.
 * 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves nodes from the [.arguments] node, specifically [order] and [direction].
 */
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/order
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/direction
